	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you like to quest, every piece of this armor is a gold mine of adventure.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, as a Shaman who loves his mana, the hat seems to be the only item worth the trouble to quest "or" buy.  5 wis is great.  The rest of the totemic armor from my own experiance and from what others have told me, is kinda fluff. Its really cool to be able to say I have a set of totemic, but it stops there for over all usefullness if you want wisdom.  <br><br>My personal recomendation... (not sure how this will apply to other races but I'll direct this at barbarians) Every piece of the Imbued northman ringmail armor set is +2 wis +1str +2sv cold.  Its wearable by tribunal only. So, we Shamans of the North were made for this stuff.  Thank you 6 hammers.  Anyway, Totemic Hat with imbued northman gear will really boost your wis and until you can quest better its quite a nice set of armor.  <br><br>Wilil Ironbear (Master Smith and 35 bar shaman)<br><br>The imbued northman Armor is made by Barbarian Smiths only.  It's our cultural armor, so if you don't want to take up smithing try looking for someone who can make the stuff.  For more info check out Northman in a search in the items on this site.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
