<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100523287680512></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100523287680512><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1484&mid=100523287680512>The question everyone has and maybe some help solving it</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1484&mid=100523287680512#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=99391><span id=Scholar>malacar</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>40 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 8th 10:21 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.11]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The question that seems to be all over this page is, "to buy or quest".&nbsp;&nbsp;Let me ask a few questions, answer them honestly for yourself, then you can decide what to do...<br><br>1) Do you enjoy playing the game to quest, or to lvl? <br><br>2) Do long camps drive you nuts?<br><br>3) Is your lvl too low to camp this bear alone?<br><br>4) Do you ever judge yourself a success in this game from completeing a quest? If so does the feeling last long enough to justify the camp time?<br><br>5) Is your time on the game limited? Such as you can only play after you get your homework done and until you have to go to bed?<br><br><br>Ok, having answered my questions to yourself, would you rather camp the bear to get the hat or follow up other persuits and keep your eyes open for one for sale?  See, that wasn't too hard.<br><br><br>Wilil Ironbear (35 Barbarian Shaman of Burtoxx, and proud owner of a totemic Hat.)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
